text: Abdelrahman Mohamed, born on 15th January 2000, is an Egyptian male handball player. He has a height of 195cm and weighs around 95kg. He is a member of the Al Ahly SC. He was the part of the Egyptian National team that won the 2019 Men's Youth World Handball Championship. He also played at 2019 Men's Junior World Handball Championship, where the team stood at 3rd position. He is recognized as one of the "world's top goalkeeper" at the 2019 Handball World Youth Championship. == References == Category:Egyptian male handball players Category:Living people Category:2000 births
